<!-- ===== FAQ teaser ===== -->
<section class="section" id="faq">
  <div class="container narrow">
    <span class="eyebrow reveal">Common questions</span>
    <h2 class="display-md reveal mt-3">Good to know.</h2>
    <div class="faq-list reveal">
      <details class="faq-item" open>
        <summary>How much does an architectural model cost? <span class="pm"></span></summary>
        <p>Architectural scale model projects typically begin around $2,000, with final pricing based on scale, level of detail, and presentation requirements. Because each model is custom-built, pricing is confirmed after reviewing project scope and intended use.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What files do you need to start? <span class="pm"></span></summary>
        <p>Dimension drawings, 3D files, or reference images are typically sufficient to begin a review. We accept CAD, PDF, Revit, Rhino, and SketchUp. If some information isn't finalized, we can still guide you to the right scope.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>Do you ship nationwide? <span class="pm"></span></summary>
        <p>Yes. Models are professionally packed and shipped across the United States and Canada for delivery to offices, sales galleries, and presentation venues. Shipping is reviewed as part of project planning.</p>
      </details>
      <details class="faq-item">
        <summary>What scale should my model be? <span class="pm"></span></summary>
        <p>Common scales include 1:50, 1:100, 1:200, and 1:500 — each suited to different needs. Scale selection is guided by model size, viewing distance, and required detail, and we provide recommendations during review.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
    <div class="mt-4"><a class="btn btn--ghost" href="/faq">All FAQs <span class="arrow">→</span></a></div>
  </div>
</section>

